    <item>
      <title>Install</title>
      <link>https://ferretlang.org/docs/tools/cli/install/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ferretlang.org/docs/tools/cli/install/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;install&#34;&gt;Install&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The Ferret CLI runs on Linux, macOS, and Windows. Full installation instructions, including how to embed Ferret as a Go library and set up browser support, are in the &lt;a href=&#34;../../getting-started/installation/&#34;&gt;Installation&lt;/a&gt; guide.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This page covers CLI-specific setup.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;from-a-prebuilt-binary&#34;&gt;From a prebuilt binary&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Download the latest release for your platform from the GitHub releases page:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/MontFerret/cli/releases&#34;&gt;https://github.com/MontFerret/cli/releases&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;After downloading, make sure the binary is available in your &lt;code&gt;PATH&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;using-the-install-script&#34;&gt;Using the install script&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-editor terminal-shortcode&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;textarea id=&#34;terminal-1-copy-clipboard&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-clipboard&#34; tabindex=&#34;-1&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/MontFerret/cli/master/install.sh | sh&lt;/textarea&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-shell&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-header&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-title&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span class=&#34;code-editor-dot&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span&gt;terminal&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-actions&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;button id=&#34;terminal-1-copy-button&#34; class=&#34;copy button is-outlined is-light code-editor-button&#34; type=&#34;button&#34;&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;        &lt;pre id=&#34;terminal-1-content&#34; class=&#34;terminal-body&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;terminal-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;terminal-prompt&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;$&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;terminal-command&#34;&gt;curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/MontFerret/cli/master/install.sh | sh&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;script&gt;&#xA;        document.addEventListener(&#39;DOMContentLoaded&#39;, function () {&#xA;            const copyBtn = document.querySelector(&#39;#terminal-1-copy-button&#39;);&#xA;            const copyClipboardEl = document.querySelector(&#39;#terminal-1-copy-clipboard&#39;);&#xA;            const terminalContent = copyClipboardEl.value;&#xA;&#xA;            function copyTextWithFallback(content) {&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.value = content;&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.focus();&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.select();&#xA;&#xA;                if (!document.execCommand(&#39;copy&#39;)) {&#xA;                    throw new Error(&#39;Could not copy terminal commands to the clipboard&#39;);&#xA;                }&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            function copyTextToClipboard(content) {&#xA;                if (navigator.clipboard &amp;&amp; navigator.clipboard.writeText) {&#xA;                    return navigator.clipboard.writeText(content).catch(() =&gt; {&#xA;                        copyTextWithFallback(content);&#xA;                    });&#xA;                }&#xA;&#xA;                copyTextWithFallback(content);&#xA;&#xA;                return Promise.resolve();&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            copyBtn.addEventListener(&#39;click&#39;, () =&gt; {&#xA;                copyTextToClipboard(terminalContent)&#xA;                    .then(() =&gt; {&#xA;                        copyBtn.textContent = &#39;Copied&#39;;&#xA;                        window.setTimeout(() =&gt; {&#xA;                            copyBtn.textContent = &#39;Copy&#39;;&#xA;                        }, 1200);&#xA;                    })&#xA;                    .catch((err) =&gt; {&#xA;                        console.error(&#39;Failed to copy terminal commands&#39;);&#xA;                        console.error(err);&#xA;                    });&#xA;            });&#xA;        }, false);&#xA;    &lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The script detects your platform, downloads the matching binary, and installs it into your PATH.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Run</title>
      <link>https://ferretlang.org/docs/tools/cli/run/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ferretlang.org/docs/tools/cli/run/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;run&#34;&gt;Run&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;run&lt;/code&gt; command executes a FQL script and prints the result to stdout. It is also available as &lt;code&gt;ferret exec&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;run-a-script-file&#34;&gt;Run a script file&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-editor terminal-shortcode&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;textarea id=&#34;terminal-9-copy-clipboard&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-clipboard&#34; tabindex=&#34;-1&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;ferret run script.fql&lt;/textarea&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-shell&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-header&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-title&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span class=&#34;code-editor-dot&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span&gt;terminal&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-actions&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;button id=&#34;terminal-9-copy-button&#34; class=&#34;copy button is-outlined is-light code-editor-button&#34; type=&#34;button&#34;&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;        &lt;pre id=&#34;terminal-9-content&#34; class=&#34;terminal-body&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;terminal-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;terminal-prompt&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;$&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;terminal-command&#34;&gt;ferret run script.fql&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;script&gt;&#xA;        document.addEventListener(&#39;DOMContentLoaded&#39;, function () {&#xA;            const copyBtn = document.querySelector(&#39;#terminal-9-copy-button&#39;);&#xA;            const copyClipboardEl = document.querySelector(&#39;#terminal-9-copy-clipboard&#39;);&#xA;            const terminalContent = copyClipboardEl.value;&#xA;&#xA;            function copyTextWithFallback(content) {&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.value = content;&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.focus();&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.select();&#xA;&#xA;                if (!document.execCommand(&#39;copy&#39;)) {&#xA;                    throw new Error(&#39;Could not copy terminal commands to the clipboard&#39;);&#xA;                }&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            function copyTextToClipboard(content) {&#xA;                if (navigator.clipboard &amp;&amp; navigator.clipboard.writeText) {&#xA;                    return navigator.clipboard.writeText(content).catch(() =&gt; {&#xA;                        copyTextWithFallback(content);&#xA;                    });&#xA;                }&#xA;&#xA;                copyTextWithFallback(content);&#xA;&#xA;                return Promise.resolve();&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            copyBtn.addEventListener(&#39;click&#39;, () =&gt; {&#xA;                copyTextToClipboard(terminalContent)&#xA;                    .then(() =&gt; {&#xA;                        copyBtn.textContent = &#39;Copied&#39;;&#xA;                        window.setTimeout(() =&gt; {&#xA;                            copyBtn.textContent = &#39;Copy&#39;;&#xA;                        }, 1200);&#xA;                    })&#xA;                    .catch((err) =&gt; {&#xA;                        console.error(&#39;Failed to copy terminal commands&#39;);&#xA;                        console.error(err);&#xA;                    });&#xA;            });&#xA;        }, false);&#xA;    &lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;evaluate-an-inline-expression&#34;&gt;Evaluate an inline expression&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Use &lt;code&gt;--eval&lt;/code&gt; (or &lt;code&gt;-e&lt;/code&gt;) to run a FQL expression directly:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>REPL</title>
      <link>https://ferretlang.org/docs/tools/cli/repl/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ferretlang.org/docs/tools/cli/repl/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;repl&#34;&gt;REPL&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;repl&lt;/code&gt; command starts an interactive FQL shell where you can type expressions and see results immediately.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-editor terminal-shortcode&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;textarea id=&#34;terminal-4-copy-clipboard&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-clipboard&#34; tabindex=&#34;-1&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;ferret repl&lt;/textarea&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-shell&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-header&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-title&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span class=&#34;code-editor-dot&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span&gt;terminal&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-actions&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;button id=&#34;terminal-4-copy-button&#34; class=&#34;copy button is-outlined is-light code-editor-button&#34; type=&#34;button&#34;&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;        &lt;pre id=&#34;terminal-4-content&#34; class=&#34;terminal-body&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;terminal-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;terminal-prompt&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;$&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;terminal-command&#34;&gt;ferret repl&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;script&gt;&#xA;        document.addEventListener(&#39;DOMContentLoaded&#39;, function () {&#xA;            const copyBtn = document.querySelector(&#39;#terminal-4-copy-button&#39;);&#xA;            const copyClipboardEl = document.querySelector(&#39;#terminal-4-copy-clipboard&#39;);&#xA;            const terminalContent = copyClipboardEl.value;&#xA;&#xA;            function copyTextWithFallback(content) {&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.value = content;&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.focus();&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.select();&#xA;&#xA;                if (!document.execCommand(&#39;copy&#39;)) {&#xA;                    throw new Error(&#39;Could not copy terminal commands to the clipboard&#39;);&#xA;                }&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            function copyTextToClipboard(content) {&#xA;                if (navigator.clipboard &amp;&amp; navigator.clipboard.writeText) {&#xA;                    return navigator.clipboard.writeText(content).catch(() =&gt; {&#xA;                        copyTextWithFallback(content);&#xA;                    });&#xA;                }&#xA;&#xA;                copyTextWithFallback(content);&#xA;&#xA;                return Promise.resolve();&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            copyBtn.addEventListener(&#39;click&#39;, () =&gt; {&#xA;                copyTextToClipboard(terminalContent)&#xA;                    .then(() =&gt; {&#xA;                        copyBtn.textContent = &#39;Copied&#39;;&#xA;                        window.setTimeout(() =&gt; {&#xA;                            copyBtn.textContent = &#39;Copy&#39;;&#xA;                        }, 1200);&#xA;                    })&#xA;                    .catch((err) =&gt; {&#xA;                        console.error(&#39;Failed to copy terminal commands&#39;);&#xA;                        console.error(err);&#xA;                    });&#xA;            });&#xA;        }, false);&#xA;    &lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The shell prints a version banner and presents a &lt;code&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; prompt:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Debug</title>
      <link>https://ferretlang.org/docs/tools/cli/debug/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ferretlang.org/docs/tools/cli/debug/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;debug&#34;&gt;Debug&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;debug&lt;/code&gt; command starts an interactive debugger for a FQL script:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-editor terminal-shortcode&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;textarea id=&#34;terminal-2-copy-clipboard&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-clipboard&#34; tabindex=&#34;-1&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;ferret debug script.fql&lt;/textarea&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-shell&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-header&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-title&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span class=&#34;code-editor-dot&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span&gt;terminal&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-actions&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;button id=&#34;terminal-2-copy-button&#34; class=&#34;copy button is-outlined is-light code-editor-button&#34; type=&#34;button&#34;&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;        &lt;pre id=&#34;terminal-2-content&#34; class=&#34;terminal-body&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;terminal-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;terminal-prompt&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;$&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;terminal-command&#34;&gt;ferret debug script.fql&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;script&gt;&#xA;        document.addEventListener(&#39;DOMContentLoaded&#39;, function () {&#xA;            const copyBtn = document.querySelector(&#39;#terminal-2-copy-button&#39;);&#xA;            const copyClipboardEl = document.querySelector(&#39;#terminal-2-copy-clipboard&#39;);&#xA;            const terminalContent = copyClipboardEl.value;&#xA;&#xA;            function copyTextWithFallback(content) {&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.value = content;&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.focus();&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.select();&#xA;&#xA;                if (!document.execCommand(&#39;copy&#39;)) {&#xA;                    throw new Error(&#39;Could not copy terminal commands to the clipboard&#39;);&#xA;                }&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            function copyTextToClipboard(content) {&#xA;                if (navigator.clipboard &amp;&amp; navigator.clipboard.writeText) {&#xA;                    return navigator.clipboard.writeText(content).catch(() =&gt; {&#xA;                        copyTextWithFallback(content);&#xA;                    });&#xA;                }&#xA;&#xA;                copyTextWithFallback(content);&#xA;&#xA;                return Promise.resolve();&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            copyBtn.addEventListener(&#39;click&#39;, () =&gt; {&#xA;                copyTextToClipboard(terminalContent)&#xA;                    .then(() =&gt; {&#xA;                        copyBtn.textContent = &#39;Copied&#39;;&#xA;                        window.setTimeout(() =&gt; {&#xA;                            copyBtn.textContent = &#39;Copy&#39;;&#xA;                        }, 1200);&#xA;                    })&#xA;                    .catch((err) =&gt; {&#xA;                        console.error(&#39;Failed to copy terminal commands&#39;);&#xA;                        console.error(err);&#xA;                    });&#xA;            });&#xA;        }, false);&#xA;    &lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The debugger compiles the script, pauses at the first executable location, and presents a &lt;code&gt;(fdb)&lt;/code&gt; prompt:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Check</title>
      <link>https://ferretlang.org/docs/tools/cli/check/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ferretlang.org/docs/tools/cli/check/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;check&#34;&gt;Check&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;check&lt;/code&gt; command compiles FQL scripts without executing them, reporting any syntax or semantic errors.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-editor terminal-shortcode&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;textarea id=&#34;terminal-5-copy-clipboard&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-clipboard&#34; tabindex=&#34;-1&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;ferret check script.fql&lt;/textarea&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-shell&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-header&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-title&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span class=&#34;code-editor-dot&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span&gt;terminal&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-actions&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;button id=&#34;terminal-5-copy-button&#34; class=&#34;copy button is-outlined is-light code-editor-button&#34; type=&#34;button&#34;&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;        &lt;pre id=&#34;terminal-5-content&#34; class=&#34;terminal-body&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;terminal-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;terminal-prompt&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;$&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;terminal-command&#34;&gt;ferret check script.fql&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;script&gt;&#xA;        document.addEventListener(&#39;DOMContentLoaded&#39;, function () {&#xA;            const copyBtn = document.querySelector(&#39;#terminal-5-copy-button&#39;);&#xA;            const copyClipboardEl = document.querySelector(&#39;#terminal-5-copy-clipboard&#39;);&#xA;            const terminalContent = copyClipboardEl.value;&#xA;&#xA;            function copyTextWithFallback(content) {&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.value = content;&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.focus();&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.select();&#xA;&#xA;                if (!document.execCommand(&#39;copy&#39;)) {&#xA;                    throw new Error(&#39;Could not copy terminal commands to the clipboard&#39;);&#xA;                }&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            function copyTextToClipboard(content) {&#xA;                if (navigator.clipboard &amp;&amp; navigator.clipboard.writeText) {&#xA;                    return navigator.clipboard.writeText(content).catch(() =&gt; {&#xA;                        copyTextWithFallback(content);&#xA;                    });&#xA;                }&#xA;&#xA;                copyTextWithFallback(content);&#xA;&#xA;                return Promise.resolve();&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            copyBtn.addEventListener(&#39;click&#39;, () =&gt; {&#xA;                copyTextToClipboard(terminalContent)&#xA;                    .then(() =&gt; {&#xA;                        copyBtn.textContent = &#39;Copied&#39;;&#xA;                        window.setTimeout(() =&gt; {&#xA;                            copyBtn.textContent = &#39;Copy&#39;;&#xA;                        }, 1200);&#xA;                    })&#xA;                    .catch((err) =&gt; {&#xA;                        console.error(&#39;Failed to copy terminal commands&#39;);&#xA;                        console.error(err);&#xA;                    });&#xA;            });&#xA;        }, false);&#xA;    &lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;If the script is valid, the command exits silently with code 0.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Fmt</title>
      <link>https://ferretlang.org/docs/tools/cli/fmt/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ferretlang.org/docs/tools/cli/fmt/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;fmt&#34;&gt;Fmt&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;fmt&lt;/code&gt; command formats FQL scripts to a consistent style.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;format-files-in-place&#34;&gt;Format files in place&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-editor terminal-shortcode&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;textarea id=&#34;terminal-8-copy-clipboard&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-clipboard&#34; tabindex=&#34;-1&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;ferret fmt script.fql&lt;/textarea&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-shell&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-header&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-title&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span class=&#34;code-editor-dot&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span&gt;terminal&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-actions&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;button id=&#34;terminal-8-copy-button&#34; class=&#34;copy button is-outlined is-light code-editor-button&#34; type=&#34;button&#34;&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;        &lt;pre id=&#34;terminal-8-content&#34; class=&#34;terminal-body&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;terminal-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;terminal-prompt&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;$&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;terminal-command&#34;&gt;ferret fmt script.fql&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;script&gt;&#xA;        document.addEventListener(&#39;DOMContentLoaded&#39;, function () {&#xA;            const copyBtn = document.querySelector(&#39;#terminal-8-copy-button&#39;);&#xA;            const copyClipboardEl = document.querySelector(&#39;#terminal-8-copy-clipboard&#39;);&#xA;            const terminalContent = copyClipboardEl.value;&#xA;&#xA;            function copyTextWithFallback(content) {&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.value = content;&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.focus();&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.select();&#xA;&#xA;                if (!document.execCommand(&#39;copy&#39;)) {&#xA;                    throw new Error(&#39;Could not copy terminal commands to the clipboard&#39;);&#xA;                }&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            function copyTextToClipboard(content) {&#xA;                if (navigator.clipboard &amp;&amp; navigator.clipboard.writeText) {&#xA;                    return navigator.clipboard.writeText(content).catch(() =&gt; {&#xA;                        copyTextWithFallback(content);&#xA;                    });&#xA;                }&#xA;&#xA;                copyTextWithFallback(content);&#xA;&#xA;                return Promise.resolve();&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            copyBtn.addEventListener(&#39;click&#39;, () =&gt; {&#xA;                copyTextToClipboard(terminalContent)&#xA;                    .then(() =&gt; {&#xA;                        copyBtn.textContent = &#39;Copied&#39;;&#xA;                        window.setTimeout(() =&gt; {&#xA;                            copyBtn.textContent = &#39;Copy&#39;;&#xA;                        }, 1200);&#xA;                    })&#xA;                    .catch((err) =&gt; {&#xA;                        console.error(&#39;Failed to copy terminal commands&#39;);&#xA;                        console.error(err);&#xA;                    });&#xA;            });&#xA;        }, false);&#xA;    &lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This overwrites the file with the formatted output.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Build</title>
      <link>https://ferretlang.org/docs/tools/cli/build/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ferretlang.org/docs/tools/cli/build/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;build&#34;&gt;Build&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;build&lt;/code&gt; command compiles FQL scripts into bytecode artifacts. Compiled artifacts skip the parsing and compilation steps at execution time.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;compile-a-script&#34;&gt;Compile a script&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-editor terminal-shortcode&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;textarea id=&#34;terminal-1-copy-clipboard&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-clipboard&#34; tabindex=&#34;-1&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;ferret build script.fql&lt;/textarea&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-shell&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-header&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-title&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span class=&#34;code-editor-dot&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span&gt;terminal&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-actions&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;button id=&#34;terminal-1-copy-button&#34; class=&#34;copy button is-outlined is-light code-editor-button&#34; type=&#34;button&#34;&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;        &lt;pre id=&#34;terminal-1-content&#34; class=&#34;terminal-body&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;terminal-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;terminal-prompt&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;$&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;terminal-command&#34;&gt;ferret build script.fql&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;script&gt;&#xA;        document.addEventListener(&#39;DOMContentLoaded&#39;, function () {&#xA;            const copyBtn = document.querySelector(&#39;#terminal-1-copy-button&#39;);&#xA;            const copyClipboardEl = document.querySelector(&#39;#terminal-1-copy-clipboard&#39;);&#xA;            const terminalContent = copyClipboardEl.value;&#xA;&#xA;            function copyTextWithFallback(content) {&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.value = content;&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.focus();&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.select();&#xA;&#xA;                if (!document.execCommand(&#39;copy&#39;)) {&#xA;                    throw new Error(&#39;Could not copy terminal commands to the clipboard&#39;);&#xA;                }&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            function copyTextToClipboard(content) {&#xA;                if (navigator.clipboard &amp;&amp; navigator.clipboard.writeText) {&#xA;                    return navigator.clipboard.writeText(content).catch(() =&gt; {&#xA;                        copyTextWithFallback(content);&#xA;                    });&#xA;                }&#xA;&#xA;                copyTextWithFallback(content);&#xA;&#xA;                return Promise.resolve();&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            copyBtn.addEventListener(&#39;click&#39;, () =&gt; {&#xA;                copyTextToClipboard(terminalContent)&#xA;                    .then(() =&gt; {&#xA;                        copyBtn.textContent = &#39;Copied&#39;;&#xA;                        window.setTimeout(() =&gt; {&#xA;                            copyBtn.textContent = &#39;Copy&#39;;&#xA;                        }, 1200);&#xA;                    })&#xA;                    .catch((err) =&gt; {&#xA;                        console.error(&#39;Failed to copy terminal commands&#39;);&#xA;                        console.error(err);&#xA;                    });&#xA;            });&#xA;        }, false);&#xA;    &lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This produces &lt;code&gt;script.fqlc&lt;/code&gt; alongside the source file.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Inspect</title>
      <link>https://ferretlang.org/docs/tools/cli/inspect/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ferretlang.org/docs/tools/cli/inspect/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;inspect&#34;&gt;Inspect&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;inspect&lt;/code&gt; command compiles a FQL script and prints a disassembly of the resulting program. This is useful for understanding how the compiler translates FQL into bytecode.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;inspect-a-script&#34;&gt;Inspect a script&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-editor terminal-shortcode&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;textarea id=&#34;terminal-6-copy-clipboard&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-clipboard&#34; tabindex=&#34;-1&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;ferret inspect script.fql&lt;/textarea&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-shell&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-header&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-title&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span class=&#34;code-editor-dot&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span&gt;terminal&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-actions&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;button id=&#34;terminal-6-copy-button&#34; class=&#34;copy button is-outlined is-light code-editor-button&#34; type=&#34;button&#34;&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;        &lt;pre id=&#34;terminal-6-content&#34; class=&#34;terminal-body&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;terminal-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;terminal-prompt&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;$&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;terminal-command&#34;&gt;ferret inspect script.fql&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;script&gt;&#xA;        document.addEventListener(&#39;DOMContentLoaded&#39;, function () {&#xA;            const copyBtn = document.querySelector(&#39;#terminal-6-copy-button&#39;);&#xA;            const copyClipboardEl = document.querySelector(&#39;#terminal-6-copy-clipboard&#39;);&#xA;            const terminalContent = copyClipboardEl.value;&#xA;&#xA;            function copyTextWithFallback(content) {&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.value = content;&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.focus();&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.select();&#xA;&#xA;                if (!document.execCommand(&#39;copy&#39;)) {&#xA;                    throw new Error(&#39;Could not copy terminal commands to the clipboard&#39;);&#xA;                }&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            function copyTextToClipboard(content) {&#xA;                if (navigator.clipboard &amp;&amp; navigator.clipboard.writeText) {&#xA;                    return navigator.clipboard.writeText(content).catch(() =&gt; {&#xA;                        copyTextWithFallback(content);&#xA;                    });&#xA;                }&#xA;&#xA;                copyTextWithFallback(content);&#xA;&#xA;                return Promise.resolve();&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            copyBtn.addEventListener(&#39;click&#39;, () =&gt; {&#xA;                copyTextToClipboard(terminalContent)&#xA;                    .then(() =&gt; {&#xA;                        copyBtn.textContent = &#39;Copied&#39;;&#xA;                        window.setTimeout(() =&gt; {&#xA;                            copyBtn.textContent = &#39;Copy&#39;;&#xA;                        }, 1200);&#xA;                    })&#xA;                    .catch((err) =&gt; {&#xA;                        console.error(&#39;Failed to copy terminal commands&#39;);&#xA;                        console.error(err);&#xA;                    });&#xA;            });&#xA;        }, false);&#xA;    &lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Without any filter flags, the full disassembly is printed: summary, bytecode instructions, constant pool, function definitions, and source spans.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Browser</title>
      <link>https://ferretlang.org/docs/tools/cli/browser/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ferretlang.org/docs/tools/cli/browser/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;browser&#34;&gt;Browser&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;browser&lt;/code&gt; command manages Chrome or Chromium instances for scripts that need a browser through the Chrome DevTools Protocol.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Most users do not need this command directly. When you pass &lt;code&gt;--browser-open&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;--browser-headless&lt;/code&gt; to &lt;code&gt;ferret run&lt;/code&gt;, the CLI starts and stops a browser automatically. The &lt;code&gt;browser&lt;/code&gt; command is useful when you want a long-lived browser that multiple script runs can share.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;open-a-browser&#34;&gt;Open a browser&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-editor terminal-shortcode&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;textarea id=&#34;terminal-6-copy-clipboard&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-clipboard&#34; tabindex=&#34;-1&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;ferret browser open&lt;/textarea&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-shell&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-header&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-title&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span class=&#34;code-editor-dot&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span&gt;terminal&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-actions&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;button id=&#34;terminal-6-copy-button&#34; class=&#34;copy button is-outlined is-light code-editor-button&#34; type=&#34;button&#34;&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;        &lt;pre id=&#34;terminal-6-content&#34; class=&#34;terminal-body&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;terminal-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;terminal-prompt&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;$&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;terminal-command&#34;&gt;ferret browser open&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;script&gt;&#xA;        document.addEventListener(&#39;DOMContentLoaded&#39;, function () {&#xA;            const copyBtn = document.querySelector(&#39;#terminal-6-copy-button&#39;);&#xA;            const copyClipboardEl = document.querySelector(&#39;#terminal-6-copy-clipboard&#39;);&#xA;            const terminalContent = copyClipboardEl.value;&#xA;&#xA;            function copyTextWithFallback(content) {&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.value = content;&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.focus();&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.select();&#xA;&#xA;                if (!document.execCommand(&#39;copy&#39;)) {&#xA;                    throw new Error(&#39;Could not copy terminal commands to the clipboard&#39;);&#xA;                }&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            function copyTextToClipboard(content) {&#xA;                if (navigator.clipboard &amp;&amp; navigator.clipboard.writeText) {&#xA;                    return navigator.clipboard.writeText(content).catch(() =&gt; {&#xA;                        copyTextWithFallback(content);&#xA;                    });&#xA;                }&#xA;&#xA;                copyTextWithFallback(content);&#xA;&#xA;                return Promise.resolve();&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            copyBtn.addEventListener(&#39;click&#39;, () =&gt; {&#xA;                copyTextToClipboard(terminalContent)&#xA;                    .then(() =&gt; {&#xA;                        copyBtn.textContent = &#39;Copied&#39;;&#xA;                        window.setTimeout(() =&gt; {&#xA;                            copyBtn.textContent = &#39;Copy&#39;;&#xA;                        }, 1200);&#xA;                    })&#xA;                    .catch((err) =&gt; {&#xA;                        console.error(&#39;Failed to copy terminal commands&#39;);&#xA;                        console.error(err);&#xA;                    });&#xA;            });&#xA;        }, false);&#xA;    &lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This starts a browser and prints the process ID. The CLI waits until the browser exits.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Config</title>
      <link>https://ferretlang.org/docs/tools/cli/config/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ferretlang.org/docs/tools/cli/config/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;config&#34;&gt;Config&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;config&lt;/code&gt; command reads and writes persistent settings that apply to all CLI commands.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;config-file&#34;&gt;Config file&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Settings are stored in &lt;code&gt;~/.ferret/config.yaml&lt;/code&gt;. The file is created automatically the first time you run any &lt;code&gt;ferret&lt;/code&gt; command.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;configuration-priority&#34;&gt;Configuration priority&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;When the same setting is specified in multiple places, the highest priority wins:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Command-line flags (highest)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Environment variables&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Config file&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Built-in defaults (lowest)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;environment-variables&#34;&gt;Environment variables&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Every config key maps to an environment variable with the &lt;code&gt;FERRET_&lt;/code&gt; prefix. Dashes become underscores:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
  </channel>
